<font color="#FF0000">SUBSTANCE ABUSE IN VIETNAM</font><br>
<tt>Wed Jun 25 16:23:46 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
The drug problem was the greatest from 1970 on to the end of the war according some of the facts  I came up with up.<br>
The vanderbilt news archives had reports generated from the top three news networks on the subject.<br>
Prior to 1970 there were, from some accounts 2-5 heroin overdoses/month during and after 1970 the overdoses  from heroin climbed to ? by some accounts 2-6 /day<br>
The drug amensty program was started late 1970 by the Gov in hopes that would encourage soldiers to stop using heroin P.S it was not effective. Someone prior to this response mentioned Cam Rahn Bay  well the drug problem was so bad there that the army constructed a concrete wall around the base hoping this would stop the flow of heroin PS that didn't work either. From appox 1971 on every GI that left country had to be tested for drugs prior to getting onto the plane  I left from Da Nang and saw this first hand.<br>
The militarys lack of experience in dealing with drugs made the problem worse then it had to be. Some articles I've read stated that the main reason for the drug problem was that soldiers were bored, When the units were closing up shop in the field and getting ready to deactivate,[ the 1st cav and the 101st were included]they became board and started smoking alot of pot. well the army didn't want the troops smoking pot so they brought in the dogs and the MPs to snif out the pot. Well when this happend many started smoking and snorting heroin because the dogs were not trained to smell heroin. heroin was smoked in formation,in chow lines and latrines. The big problem with the heroin was that it was 99% pure thats why so many GIs were strung out. You became addicted over night. so army got its way they stopped the pot but the party continued with the heroin. The sad fact was,as the army was testing for drug addicts the bigger problem was the  new alcoholics that were born during the Vietnam war, They were allowed to get onthe plane with a drink in their hand. Now Thats a  can of worms yet to be opened. Thanks and yes this was a flash back. forgive my spelling
